# Quick Docker Command Reference for Radio Calico

## Production Commands
make build              # Build production images
make up                 # Start production services
make down               # Stop production services
make logs               # View production logs
make restart            # Restart production services
make ps                 # Show running containers

## Development Commands
make dev                # Start development environment
make dev-build          # Build and start dev environment
make dev-down           # Stop development environment
make dev-logs           # View development logs
make dev-test           # Run tests in container
make dev-shell          # Open shell in container

## Database Commands
make backup             # Backup production database
make restore            # Restore from backup.sql
make db-shell           # PostgreSQL shell (production)
make db-shell-dev       # PostgreSQL shell (development)

## Security Commands
make security           # Run security audit
make security-check     # Security audit (fail on moderate+)
make security-fix       # Automatically fix security issues
make security-scan      # Full security scan (audit + outdated)
make security-docker    # Run security scan in Docker
make security-report    # Generate JSON security report

## Maintenance Commands
make clean              # Remove containers and volumes
make clean-images       # Remove Docker images
make clean-all          # Full cleanup
make health             # Check service health

## Direct Docker Commands (without make)

# Production
docker-compose up -d
docker-compose down
docker-compose logs -f app
docker-compose ps

# Development
docker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d
docker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml exec app npm test
docker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml exec app sh
docker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml down

# Database access
docker-compose exec postgres psql -U admin -d prototype_db
docker-compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml exec postgres psql -U admin -d prototype_db

# Backup/Restore
docker-compose exec -T postgres pg_dump -U admin prototype_db > backup.sql
docker-compose exec -T postgres psql -U admin prototype_db < backup.sql

## URLs
Application: http://localhost:3000
Health Check: http://localhost:3000/api/health
API Docs: See README.md

